cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation and optical flow, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also proposes a technique for augmenting existing CNN architectures, which falls under the domain of machine learning and deep learning, and hence cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions benchmark datasets such as CamVid and Cityscapes, which are commonly used in multimedia research, indicating a possible sub-category of cs.MM. Finally, the paper discusses the use of optical flow for warping representations across time, which is a technique commonly used in robotics and autonomous systems, suggesting a possible sub-category of cs.RO.
